The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Tinplate gets new chairman
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Tinplate gets new chairman
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, Jan. 15: Koushik Chatterjee, chief financial officer of the Tata Steel group, has been appointed the chairman of Tinplate Company India Ltd.        
	Chatterjee, who is already on the companys board, will replace former Tata Steel managing director B. Muthuraman. The company announced the board rejig yesterday. Muthuraman, who became the vice-chairman of Tata Steel after completing his term as the managing director, has stepped down from the Tinplate board.         
	Chatterjee, one of the youngest senior executives within the Tata group, shot to limelight after playing a key role in the acquisition of Corus in 2008. He was also instrumental in the financial restructuring of Tinplate and putting it back on the growth track.         
	The company has posted a marginal rise in topline at Rs 196.94 crore in the third quarter against Rs 180.81 crore a year ago. However, profit rose sharply to Rs 22.25 crore from Rs 2.54 crore a year ago.                                                                                                                                       
